  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.union:over{C}]\nDefines: U is \\set\nwhen: C is \\set\nexpresses:\n. forAll: x is \\set\n  then:\n  . have:\n    . exists: A is \\set\n      suchThat:\n      . A \"in\" C\n      . x \"in\" A\n    iff: x \"in\" U\nDocumented:\n. called: \"union over $C?$\"\n. written: \"\\bigcup_{A \\in C?} A\"\n. description: \"The union over a collection $C$ of sets, guaranteed by the axiom of unions: $x \\in \\bigcup_{A \\in C} A$ if and only if there exists $A \\in C$ such that $x \\in A$. Its uniqueness follows from the axiom of extension.\"\nId: \"d74b5a03-d4c5-4257-b076-f020efc36af1\"",
